HhBsypuBSkfgUBNX0RAOt6Zer0gfkRnkmwmpUA0=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating imports in Scala**\\n\\nI'm realizing that I should always import classes and use them without qualified names. I had to fully qualify `scala.concurrent.duration` before due to a conflict. I wonder if I can just import `scala.concurrent.duration.FiniteDuration` instead. Actually, I should note that the create function returns a Duration. I'll need to keep this in mind while managing my imports more effectively!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `FileAndResourceDirectives#getFromResource`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test:\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http_2.13/1.3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_pekko/pekko_http_2_13/FileAndResourceDirectivesTest.java`\n- Removed scaffold placeholder test:\n  - `tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-http_2.13/1.3.0/src/test/java/org_apache_pekko/pekko_http_2_13/Pekko_http_2_13Test.java`\n\nWhat the new test covers:\n- Uses Pekko HTTP Java DSL public API.\n- Builds a `getFromResource(...)` route with an explicit `ClassLoader`.\n- Starts a localhost server on an ephemeral port.\n- Performs a real HTTP GET and asserts the served resource body.\n- Unbinds the server and terminates the `ActorSystem` with bounded waits.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_001f8e64392c9df1016a2b601ef1fc81948473d3ff6ef8467c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1235, "output": 1107, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37670, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781227522690, "responseId": "resp_001f8e64392c9df1016a2b60035bcc8194b51cebb335c5f2a6"}}
